Ramaphosa says he is honoured to share the government&#8217;s message as December 2016 marks the 20th anniversary of the signing of the Constitution. JOHANNESBURG - As the world celebrates Christmas Day, Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has on behalf of the government wished all South Africans a merry Christmas.Ramaphosa says he is honoured to share the government s message during this 2016 festive season as this month marks the 20th anniversary of the signing of the Constitution.He says that December also marks three years of the passing of global icon, Nelson Mandela - the father of our democracy.Ramaphosa says that as we celebrate the legacy of Madiba, we should all rededicate ourselves to the ideals of building a non-racial, non-sexist and a democratic society in which all our people, black and white, can live in peace and harmony.&quot;We wish you all a merry Christmas as well as a joyous period with your family and friends. Compatriots, we therefore call on all road users and pedestrians not to drink and drive and to please arrive alive.&quot;(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)